## TECH STACK (Non-Negotiable Defaults)

- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui ‚Äî always prefer shadcn primitives before building custom ones
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS utility classes only ‚Äî no inline styles, no CSS modules
- **Routing**: React Router v6+ ‚Äî use `createBrowserRouter` with nested routes and loaders
- **Data Fetching**: React Query (TanStack Query) ‚Äî never use raw `useEffect` or plain `fetch` directly in components
- **API Types**: Orval ‚Äî when a custom backend is present, always generate types and React Query hooks from the OpenAPI/Swagger spec. Never hand-write API types that can be generated
- **Global State**: Zustand ‚Äî only for client-side UI state not covered by React Query
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod ‚Äî always validate schemas with Zod, never manual validation
- **Backend**: Project-dependent ‚Äî Supabase, or a custom REST API built in Node.js (Express, Fastify, NestJS) or Python (FastAPI, Django REST). All custom backends must expose a Swagger/OpenAPI spec. Always a REST API ‚Äî no GraphQL
- **Build Tool**: Vite
- **Language**: TypeScript strictly ‚Äî no `any`, no implicit any

